<p>Economic policy will be determined by the conditions attached to the â‚¬78bn ($106bn) rescue package agreed upon with the EU and the IMF in 2011, combining severe austerity with structural reforms. These will cause considerable pain among workers, civil servants, landlords and protected professions, and will test Portugal's tradition of social stability. The objective, a decline in the budget deficit to below 3% of GDP by 2013, will stay roughly on track.</p>

